<br>
When i was a wee strugglin' chanter, I used to make good money (a plat!) bindin' folks. That money came at a time when spells were expensive and income was rare.<br>
<br>
Casters (particularly the cleric, but to a great degree the enchanter, too) need to med between pulls. If the cleric ain't meddin' then the whole group is slowed up. What that means is the cleric almost never loots. The enchanter rarely loots. These classes do need money to afford spells, but the cleric is particularly hosed 'cause they also need armor. Once ya make it to about level 20 or 30, the spells become quite affordable and money becomes less of an issue.<br>
<br>
Nowadays, I can afford my spells with the little cash I scrounge up so I'm happy. But, Uriel, yer theory that every class is entitled to even loot just don't work fer the most part. The only groups where I git fair loot (and that includes when I group with you folks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) is when I hunt with Lunacy. They have a largely guild-wide master looter policy. That means when guild members group together, we designate a master looter who shares out the goods at the end of the night. Of course, sometimes everyone fergits about sharin' the loot at the end so it ain't done. That's when someone walks away accidentally rich. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, if I walk away with more than 1pp of loot for a few hours of groupin', then I consider myself lucky. I often walk away with less. But that don't matter to me 'cause my spells are so cheap (relatively) these days.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> BUT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, I'll have to say, I like this change Verant made. Waitin' an hour fer a caster to wander by just plain stinks. <p><BR>
